<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="207" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1977,2038]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,1400]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="207" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1977,2002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Fronto-clypeus strongly depressed up to antennal sockets, with carinae convergent posteriad. Antennomere 
<date box="[311,357,2014,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
III 
<number box="[347,357,2014,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
/ 
<number box="[367,383,2014,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="4.0">4</number>
longer than pedicel. Maxillary palpomere IV 
<date box="[905,932,2014,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<number box="[905,918,2014,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
longer than III. Pronotum subparallel-sided, posterior angle weakly developed and acute. Elytron with humeral macula orangish-yellow. Abdominal sternum V straight; VI with lantern 
<number box="[433,443,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[453,469,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="2.0">2</number>
length and 
<number box="[605,616,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[626,640,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
width of this sternum; abdominal sternum VII as long as 
<number box="[1302,1314,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1323,1337,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="4.0">4</number>
sternum length and as wide as 
<number box="[397,408,224,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[419,433,224,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
sternum width..
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Colouration</emphasis>
. (Fig. 
<number box="[422,434,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
) Integument from dark-brown to yellowish-brown. Pronotum from entirely dark-brown to entirely yellowish-brown, with expansions pale-yellow. Elytron dark-brown, with suture and outer margin paleyellow, humeral macula orangish-yellow. Pygidum dark-brown, with lateral margins and median lobe pale-yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,367,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Head</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[292,381,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 40" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1758,1781]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,204,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1737]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 40. Frons shape drawings 23 Amydetes agnita. 24 A. apicalis. 25 A. discissa. 26 A. fastigiata. 27 A. fucata. 28 A. lucioloides. 29 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 30 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 31 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov.. 32 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 33 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 34 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 35 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 36 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 37 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 38 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 39 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 40 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 250 µm. DBA = distance between antennifers antennifers. DBAS = distance between antennal sockets." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252107/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
Fig. 
<number box="[351,381,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="23.42">23</number>
</figureCitation>
, 42) Fronto-clypeus strongly depressed up to antennal sockets, with carinae convergent posteriad, anterior margin 
<number box="[463,474,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[485,499,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
wider than distance between antennal sockets and slightly wider than distance between antennifers. Antenna with 
<number box="[570,598,440,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="29.0">29</number>
antennomeres (n= 
<number box="[820,835,440,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="2.0">2</number>
); antennomere III at least 
<number box="[1155,1165,440,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1175,1191,440,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="4.0">4</number>
longer than pedicel, flabellum 
<date box="[265,293,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<number box="[265,279,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than antennomere III. Labrum slightly emarginate. Maxillary palpomere IV 
<date box="[1232,1260,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<number box="[1232,1245,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
longer than III, as long as labial palpomere III. Gular sutures separeted by maxillary palpomere IV width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Thorax</emphasis>
. (Fig. 
<number box="[377,455,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="61.79">61, 79</number>
) Pronotum subparallel-sided, posterior angle acute and weakly projected, slightly deflexed; setigerous punctures irregularly separete 0.5– 
<date box="[782,806,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<number box="[782,791,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
x
</date>
the diameter of a puncture. Hypomeron 
<date box="[1271,1299,584,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<number box="[1271,1285,584,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than high. Scutelum subparallel-sided. Elytron subparallel-sided; marginal costa with anterior margin not projected. Mesosternum with posterior projection acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,692,717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Abdomen</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[344,458,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 107 – 115" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1856,1879]" captionTargetBox="[233,1331,520,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[221,1345,517,1815]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 107 – 115. Abdomen, ventral. Note the lanterns and posterior margin of abdominal sternite V and VIII. 107 Amydetes agnita. 108 A. apicalis. 109 A. discissa. 110 A. fastigiata. 111 A. fucata. 112 A. lucioloides. 113 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 114 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 115 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov.. Scale. 1 mm. AS VI = abdominal sternite VI. AS VII = abdominal sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252113/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Figs. 107</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[476,520,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 125 – 133" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[238,1332,458,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[233,1354,437,1885]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 125 – 133. Pygidium, dorsal. 125 Amydetes agnita. 126 A. apicalis. 127 A. discissa. 128 A. fastigiata. 129 A. fucata. 130 A. lucioloides. 131 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 132 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 133 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov.. Scale. 500 µm. A. Anterior, P. Posterior" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252115/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">125</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[539,638,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 147 – 159" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[296,1293,185,1249]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[282,1305,177,1254]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 147 – 159. Terminália. FIGURES 147, 151 and 155 syntergite (dorsal) and abdominal sternite IX (ventral). FIGURES 147 – 150, 151 – 154, 155 – 159 Aedeagus (dorsal. 148, 152, 156. ventral. 149, 153 and 157. lateral. 150, 154, 158) and ventral view of phallum (159). FIGURES 147 – 150 A. agnita. 151 – 154 A. apicalis. 155 – 159 A. discissa. Scale. 200 µm. S = syntergite, TA IX = abdominal tergite IX. AT IX = abdominal tergite X. AS IX = abdominal sternite X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252118/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
147– 
<number box="[596,638,692,717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="150.0">150</number>
</figureCitation>
) Abdominal sternum V with posterior margin straight. Abdominal sternum VI with lantern as long as 
<number box="[550,560,728,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[571,587,728,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="2.0">2</number>
sternum length and as wide as 
<number box="[944,955,728,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[966,980,728,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
sternum width. Abdominal sternum VII with lantern as long as 
<number box="[434,446,764,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[455,469,764,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="4.0">4</number>
sternum length and as wide as 
<number box="[854,865,764,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[876,890,764,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
sternum width. Abdominal sternum VIII with posterior margin straight. Pygidium with median lobe rounded, as wide as 
<number box="[1011,1024,799,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1033,1046,799,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="5.0">5</number>
width of posterior margin; lateral lobe rudimentary. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,497,836,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Terminalia:</emphasis>
Syntergite with lateral margins convergent posteriad, anterior margin truncate, and posterior margin asymmetric; suture between abdominal tergites IX and X indistinct. Abdominal sternum IX almost 
<date box="[232,260,908,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<number box="[232,246,908,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than syntergite, almost 
<date box="[605,633,908,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">
<number box="[605,618,908,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
longer than wide, bristled at posterior 
<number box="[1065,1076,908,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1088,1103,908,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
, with lateral margins strongly divergent posteriad at the anterior 
<number box="[582,593,944,968]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[604,621,944,968]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="2.0">2</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[641,765,943,968]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Weakly sclerotized. Phallobase asymmetric. Parameres constricted basally, close-set subapically. Phallus and paramere apically rounded. Phallus 
<number box="[1150,1160,980,1004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1171,1185,980,1004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="207" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than paramere. Ventral plate sinuous, weakly sclerotized.
</paragraph>
